<br>
This is the table that I originally compiled, as this was the number originally printed on the weapons.  There was no correlation that seemed to make a formula possible.  For instance, the bonus could be the same for a range of delays, then jump by 2-3 to another range of delays.  The delay at which the jump occurred varied by level.  The amount of the jump varied by level.  The size of each range varied by level.  The number of ranges varied by level.<br>
<br>
As far as the differences between what is posted and what you see, please confirm and post your results as well, and we can discuss.  My assumptions on the damage bonus are based on a Developer's Corner thread when they were originally upgraded last year.  At that time the programmer stated that class, level, and delay were the only factors.  Perhaps they changed something since then without telling us. <p><center>
